</a>
</h2>
<ul>
<li><b>Tiling space and slabs with acute tetrahedra</b>.<br>
D. Eppstein,
<a href="//torus.math.uiuc.edu/jms/">J. M. Sullivan</a>,
and <a href="//www.cs.duke.edu/~ungor/">A. &Uuml;ng&ouml;r</a>.<br>
<a href="//arxiv.org/abs/cs.CG/0302027">arXiv:cs.CG/0302027</a>.<br>
<a href="//doi.org/10.1016/j.comgeo.2003.11.003">
<i>Comp. Geom. Theory &amp; Applications</i> 27 (3): 237&ndash;255, 2004</a>.
<p>
We show it is possible to
<a href="geom-tri.html">triangulate</a> three-dimensional space using only
tetrahedra with acute dihedral angles. We present several constructions
to achieve this, including one in which all dihedral angles are less
than 77.08 degrees, and another which tiles a slab in space.
<p>
(<a href="//www.ics.uci.edu/~eppstein/bibs/eppstein.html#Tiling space and slabs with acute tetrahedra">BibTeX</a>)
<p>
